# Cursor Rules for charmbracelet/bubbles

## Project Context

This is Bubbles, a Go TUI component library built on Bubble Tea (charm.land/bubbletea/v2). Module path: charm.land/bubbles/v2. Each component is its own Go package in a dedicated directory.

## Architecture Pattern

Every component follows the Elm Architecture with this structure:

- Model struct: holds all component state. Public fields for user config, private fields for internal state.
- New() constructor: returns a configured Model. Newer components use functional options: New(opts ...Option) where Option is func(*Model).
- Update(msg tea.Msg) (Model, tea.Cmd): processes messages. ALWAYS returns concrete Model type, never tea.Model.
- View() string: renders to string using lipgloss styles.
- Init() tea.Cmd: OPTIONAL. Only for components needing initial commands (filepicker, viewport, progress, timer, stopwatch).
- KeyMap struct + DefaultKeyMap(): keybinding definitions using key.Binding.
- Styles struct + DefaultStyles(): lipgloss styling with sensible defaults.

## Component List and Composition

- cursor: virtual blinking cursor (used by textinput, textarea)
- filepicker: filesystem browser with directory navigation
- help: auto-generated keybinding help (consumes help.KeyMap interface)
- key: keybinding definitions and matching (non-visual, foundational)
- list: browsable list with filtering/pagination (composes paginator, spinner, textinput, help)
- paginator: pagination logic and indicators
- progress: animated progress bar with gradient colors (uses harmonica for spring animation)
- spinner: animated spinner with preset frame sets
- stopwatch: count-up timer
- table: tabular data with scrolling (composes viewport, help)
- textarea: multi-line text editor (composes cursor, viewport)
- textinput: single-line input with suggestions (composes cursor)
- timer: countdown timer
- viewport: scrollable content area with soft-wrap and gutters

## Key Interfaces

list.Item: FilterValue() string -- required for anything in a list.
list.ItemDelegate: Render(w io.Writer, m Model, index int, item Item) + Height() int + Spacing() int + Update(msg tea.Msg, m *Model) tea.Cmd.
help.KeyMap: ShortHelp() []key.Binding + FullHelp() [][]key.Binding.

## Import Paths (v2 -- always use these)

charm.land/bubbles/v2/<component>
charm.land/bubbletea/v2 (aliased as tea)
charm.land/lipgloss/v2

Never use github.com/charmbracelet/bubbles -- that is v1.

## Code Style

- Formatter: gofumpt + goimports (enforced by golangci-lint v2.9)
- All comments end with a period (godot linter)
- All exported symbols have doc comments
- Wrap errors from external packages (wrapcheck)
- Exhaustive switches on enum types (exhaustive)
- Package-level doc comment on every package

## Testing

- Table-driven tests with map[string]struct{} and named subtests
- Golden file tests for View() output using github.com/charmbracelet/x/exp/golden
- Golden files stored in <component>/testdata/<TestName>/<subtest>.golden
- Regenerate golden files: go test ./... -update
- Tests construct models, pipe messages through Update(), assert View() output

## Animated Component ID Pattern

Spinner, progress, cursor, stopwatch, timer, and filepicker each maintain an atomic ID counter (lastID + nextID()). Each model instance gets a unique ID at construction. Tick/blink messages carry the sender's ID so only the correct instance processes them.

## Build Commands

go test ./...                    # run all tests
go test ./... -update            # update golden files
golangci-lint run                # lint
task test                        # Taskfile shortcut for tests
task lint                        # Taskfile shortcut for lint

## Internal Packages (not importable externally)

internal/memoization/ -- generic cache for textarea render optimization
internal/runeutil/ -- rune sanitization and display width utilities

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

- Do not return tea.Model from Update(). Return the concrete Model type.
- Do not add Init() unless the component genuinely needs an initial command.
- Do not use github.com/charmbracelet/bubbles imports. This is v2 with charm.land paths.
- Do not forget DefaultKeyMap() and DefaultStyles() when adding new configurable bindings or styles.
- Do not use global mutable state except the atomic ID counter pattern for animated components.
- Do not skip the godot linter: end all comments with periods.
